on 10/8/03 12:45 PM, Blake Haralson at nakedclimber(-at-)yahoo.com wrote:

> Hi listees,
> When decelerating and down shifting, I am getting the rapid popping sound from
> the rear. From my experience with this list, I know that the most common cause
> is an exhaust leak. My question is: If I had an exhaust leak that was too
> small to be noisy or heard, could it still cause this problem? Also, what are
> the other common causes?
> Thanks in advance for the help.

You might to search the archives.  I recently had this problem, and it was
caused by a combination of damaged intake manifold gasket and a leaking
power brake vacuum hose.  Look for leaks everywhere.

